      "display_title": "Issue #102: Handle Issue App Crashes with Insta360 SDK Error 444 During Camera Connection on IOS",
      "main_description_html": "<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"images/image-2e89ad5c-0663-40a1-8d55-b4ccf6c373de.png\"><img width=\"221\" height=\"224\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"images/image-2e89ad5c-0663-40a1-8d55-b4ccf6c373de.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto; max-height: 224px;; aspect-ratio: 221 / 224; background-color: var(--bgColor-muted); border-radius: 6px\" class=\"js-gh-image-fallback\"></a>\n<h2 dir=\"auto\">Description</h2>\n<p dir=\"auto\">A user reported an app crash on iOS when attempting to connect to the Insta360 camera. Instead of establishing a connection, the connection process fails and throws a native SDK error on the screen.</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Error Message Displayed:<br>\nThe operation couldn't be completed. (com.insta360.camerasdk.error error 444.)</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Environment &amp; Details</p>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>Platform: iOS</li>\n<li>Component: Insta360 Camera Connection Module / SDK</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Acceptance Criteria</p>\n<ol dir=\"auto\">\n<li>The iOS application successfully connects to the Insta360 camera without throwing error 444.</li>\n<li>If the connection fails due to external factors (camera off, WiFi blocked), the app handles the error gracefully instead of crashing.</li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">QA Tester Summary - Issue <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"4764638693\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/GoThruMedia/streeteditor-flutter/issues/102\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/GoThruMedia/streeteditor-flutter/issues/102/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/GoThruMedia/streeteditor-flutter/issues/102\">#102</a>: Handle Issue App Crashes with Insta360 SDK Error 444 During Camera Connection on IOS</h3>\n<ul class=\"contains-task-list\">\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"\" disabled=\"\" class=\"task-list-item-checkbox\" aria-label=\"Completed task\" checked=\"\"> 1. The iOS application successfully connects to the Insta360 camera without throwing error 444.</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><strong>Android</strong></p>\n<details open=\"\" class=\"details-reset border rounded-2\">\n  <summary class=\"tmp-px-3 py-2\">\n    <svg aria-hidden=\"true\" data-component=\"Octicon\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" data-view-component=\"true\" class=\"octicon octicon-device-camera-video\">\n    <path d=\"M16 3.75v8.5a.75.75 0 0 1-1.136.643L11 10.575v.675A1.75 1.75 0 0 1 9.25 13h-7.5A1.75 1.75 0 0 1 0 11.25v-6.5C0 3.784.784 3 1.75 3h7.5c.966 0 1.75.784 1.75 1.75v.675l3.864-2.318A.75.75 0 0 1 16 3.75Zm-6.5 1a.25.25 0 0 0-.25-.25h-7.5a.25.25 0 0 0-.25.25v6.5c0 .138.112.25.25.25h7.5a.25.25 0 0 0 .25-.25v-6.5ZM11 8.825l3.5 2.1v-5.85l-3.5 2.1Z\"></path>\n</svg>\n    <span class=\"m-1\">WhatsApp.Video.2026-06-30.at.18.14.07.mp4</span>\n    <span class=\"dropdown-caret\"></span>\n  </summary>\n\n  <video src=\"videos/video-860672a7-ed69-4789-a529-12ee3c134cc6.mp4\" data-canonical-src=\"videos/video-860672a7-ed69-4789-a529-12ee3c134cc6.mp4\" controls=\"controls\" muted=\"muted\" class=\"d-block rounded-bottom-2 border-top width-fit\" style=\"max-height:640px; min-height: 200px\">\n\n  </video>\n</details>\n\n<ul class=\"contains-task-list\">\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"\" disabled=\"\" class=\"task-list-item-checkbox\" aria-label=\"Incomplete task\"> 2. If the connection fails due to external factors (camera off, WiFi blocked), the app handles the error gracefully instead of crashing.</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><em>🐞[360 Camera Connection] \"Phone Wi-Fi On\" is incorrectly marked as completed when the device is connected to the internet instead of the 360 camera Wi-Fi (4:10)</em></p>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><strong>Android</strong></p>\n<details open=\"\" class=\"details-reset border rounded-2\">\n  <summary class=\"tmp-px-3 py-2\">\n    <svg aria-hidden=\"tr